{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Ever since I was a little girl"},{"time":3000,"text":"seeing \"Star Wars\" for the first time,"},{"time":5000,"text":"I've been fascinated by this idea"},{"time":7000,"text":"of personal robots."},{"time":9000,"text":"And as a little girl,"},{"time":11000,"text":"I loved the idea of a robot that interacted with us"},{"time":13000,"text":"much more like a helpful, trusted sidekick --"},{"time":16000,"text":"something that would delight us, enrich our lives"},{"time":18000,"text":"and help us save a galaxy or two."},{"time":22000,"text":"I knew robots like that didn't really exist,"},{"time":25000,"text":"but I knew I wanted to build them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27000,"text":"So 20 years pass --"},{"time":29000,"text":"I am now a graduate student at MIT"},{"time":31000,"text":"studying artificial intelligence,"},{"time":33000,"text":"the year is 1997,"},{"time":35000,"text":"and NASA has just landed the first robot on Mars."},{"time":38000,"text":"But robots are still not in our home, ironically."},{"time":41000,"text":"And I remember thinking about"},{"time":43000,"text":"all the reasons why that was the case."},{"time":45000,"text":"But one really struck me."},{"time":47000,"text":"Robotics had really been about interacting with things,"},{"time":50000,"text":"not with people --"},{"time":52000,"text":"certainly not in a social way that would be natural for us"},{"time":54000,"text":"and would really help people accept robots"},{"time":56000,"text":"into our daily lives."},{"time":58000,"text":"For me, that was the white space; that's what robots could not do yet."},{"time":61000,"text":"And so that year, I started to build this robot, Kismet,"},{"time":64000,"text":"the world's first social robot."},{"time":67000,"text":"Three years later --"},{"time":69000,"text":"a lot of programming,"},{"time":71000,"text":"working with other graduate students in the lab --"},{"time":73000,"text":"Kismet was ready to start interacting with people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75000,"text":"(Video) Scientist: I want to show you something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77000,"text":"Kismet: (Nonsense)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":79000,"text":"Scientist: This is a watch that my girlfriend gave me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82000,"text":"Kismet: (Nonsense)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":84000,"text":"Scientist: Yeah, look, it's got a little blue light in it too."},{"time":86000,"text":"I almost lost it this week."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89000,"text":"Cynthia Breazeal: So Kismet interacted with people"},{"time":92000,"text":"like kind of a non-verbal child or pre-verbal child,"},{"time":95000,"text":"which I assume was fitting because it was really the first of its kind."},{"time":98000,"text":"It didn't speak language, but it didn't matter."},{"time":100000,"text":"This little robot was somehow able"},{"time":102000,"text":"to tap into something deeply social within us --"},{"time":105000,"text":"and with that, the promise of an entirely new way"},{"time":107000,"text":"we could interact with robots."}]},{"cues":[{"time":109000,"text":"So over the past several years"},{"time":111000,"text":"I've been continuing to explore this interpersonal dimension of robots,"},{"time":113000,"text":"now at the media lab"},{"time":115000,"text":"with my own team of incredibly talented students."},{"time":117000,"text":"And one of my favorite robots is Leonardo."},{"time":120000,"text":"We developed Leonardo in collaboration with Stan Winston Studio."},{"time":123000,"text":"And so I want to show you a special moment for me of Leo."},{"time":126000,"text":"This is Matt Berlin interacting with Leo,"},{"time":128000,"text":"introducing Leo to a new object."},{"time":130000,"text":"And because it's new, Leo doesn't really know what to make of it."},{"time":133000,"text":"But sort of like us, he can actually learn about it"},{"time":135000,"text":"from watching Matt's reaction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138000,"text":"(Video) Matt Berlin: Hello, Leo."},{"time":143000,"text":"Leo, this is Cookie Monster."},{"time":149000,"text":"Can you find Cookie Monster?"},{"time":157000,"text":"Leo, Cookie Monster is very bad."},{"time":161000,"text":"He's very bad, Leo."},{"time":165000,"text":"Cookie Monster is very, very bad."},{"time":172000,"text":"He's a scary monster."},{"time":174000,"text":"He wants to get your cookies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":179000,"text":"CB: All right, so Leo and Cookie"},{"time":182000,"text":"might have gotten off to a little bit of a rough start,"},{"time":184000,"text":"but they get along great now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":187000,"text":"So what I've learned"},{"time":189000,"text":"through building these systems"},{"time":191000,"text":"is that robots are actually"},{"time":193000,"text":"a really intriguing social technology,"},{"time":195000,"text":"where it's actually their ability"},{"time":197000,"text":"to push our social buttons"},{"time":199000,"text":"and to interact with us like a partner"},{"time":201000,"text":"that is a core part of their functionality."},{"time":204000,"text":"And with that shift in thinking, we can now start to imagine"},{"time":206000,"text":"new questions, new possibilities for robots"},{"time":209000,"text":"that we might not have thought about otherwise."},{"time":212000,"text":"But what do I mean when I say \"push our social buttons?\""},{"time":214000,"text":"Well, one of the things that we've learned"},{"time":216000,"text":"is that, if we design these robots to communicate with us"},{"time":218000,"text":"using the same body language,"},{"time":220000,"text":"the same sort of non-verbal cues that people use --"},{"time":222000,"text":"like Nexi, our humanoid robot, is doing here --"},{"time":225000,"text":"what we find is that people respond to robots"},{"time":227000,"text":"a lot like they respond to people."},{"time":229000,"text":"People use these cues to determine things like how persuasive someone is,"},{"time":232000,"text":"how likable, how engaging,"},{"time":234000,"text":"how trustworthy."},{"time":236000,"text":"It turns out it's the same for robots."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238000,"text":"It's turning out now"},{"time":240000,"text":"that robots are actually becoming a really interesting new scientific tool"},{"time":243000,"text":"to understand human behavior."},{"time":245000,"text":"To answer questions like, how is it that, from a brief encounter,"},{"time":248000,"text":"we're able to make an estimate of how trustworthy another person is?"},{"time":251000,"text":"Mimicry's believed to play a role, but how?"},{"time":254000,"text":"Is it the mimicking of particular gestures that matters?"},{"time":257000,"text":"It turns out it's really hard"},{"time":259000,"text":"to learn this or understand this from watching people"},{"time":261000,"text":"because when we interact we do all of these cues automatically."},{"time":264000,"text":"We can't carefully control them because they're subconscious for us."},{"time":266000,"text":"But with the robot, you can."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268000,"text":"And so in this video here --"},{"time":270000,"text":"this is a video taken from David DeSteno's lab at Northeastern University."},{"time":273000,"text":"He's a psychologist we've been collaborating with."},{"time":275000,"text":"There's actually a scientist carefully controlling Nexi's cues"},{"time":278000,"text":"to be able to study this question."},{"time":281000,"text":"And the bottom line is -- the reason why this works is"},{"time":283000,"text":"because it turns out people just behave like people"},{"time":285000,"text":"even when interacting with a robot."},{"time":288000,"text":"So given that key insight,"},{"time":290000,"text":"we can now start to imagine"},{"time":292000,"text":"new kinds of applications for robots."},{"time":295000,"text":"For instance, if robots do respond to our non-verbal cues,"},{"time":298000,"text":"maybe they would be a cool, new communication technology."},{"time":302000,"text":"So imagine this:"},{"time":304000,"text":"What about a robot accessory for your cellphone?"},{"time":306000,"text":"You call your friend, she puts her handset in a robot,"},{"time":308000,"text":"and, bam! You're a MeBot --"},{"time":310000,"text":"you can make eye contact, you can talk with your friends,"},{"time":313000,"text":"you can move around, you can gesture --"},{"time":315000,"text":"maybe the next best thing to really being there, or is it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":318000,"text":"To explore this question,"},{"time":320000,"text":"my student, Siggy Adalgeirsson, did a study"},{"time":323000,"text":"where we brought human participants, people, into our lab"},{"time":326000,"text":"to do a collaborative task"},{"time":328000,"text":"with a remote collaborator."},{"time":330000,"text":"The task involved things"},{"time":332000,"text":"like looking at a set of objects on the table,"},{"time":334000,"text":"discussing them in terms of their importance and relevance to performing a certain task --"},{"time":337000,"text":"this ended up being a survival task --"},{"time":339000,"text":"and then rating them in terms"},{"time":341000,"text":"of how valuable and important they thought they were."},{"time":343000,"text":"The remote collaborator was an experimenter from our group"},{"time":346000,"text":"who used one of three different technologies"},{"time":348000,"text":"to interact with the participants."},{"time":350000,"text":"The first was just the screen."},{"time":352000,"text":"This is just like video conferencing today."},{"time":355000,"text":"The next was to add mobility -- so, have the screen on a mobile base."},{"time":358000,"text":"This is like, if you're familiar with any of the telepresence robots today --"},{"time":361000,"text":"this is mirroring that situation."},{"time":364000,"text":"And then the fully expressive MeBot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":366000,"text":"So after the interaction,"},{"time":368000,"text":"we asked people to rate their quality of interaction"},{"time":371000,"text":"with the technology, with a remote collaborator"},{"time":373000,"text":"through this technology, in a number of different ways."},{"time":376000,"text":"We looked at psychological involvement --"},{"time":378000,"text":"how much empathy did you feel for the other person?"},{"time":380000,"text":"We looked at overall engagement."},{"time":382000,"text":"We looked at their desire to cooperate."},{"time":384000,"text":"And this is what we see when they use just the screen."},{"time":387000,"text":"It turns out, when you add mobility -- the ability to roll around the table --"},{"time":390000,"text":"you get a little more of a boost."},{"time":392000,"text":"And you get even more of a boost when you add the full expression."},{"time":395000,"text":"So it seems like this physical, social embodiment"},{"time":397000,"text":"actually really makes a difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399000,"text":"Now let's try to put this into a little bit of context."},{"time":402000,"text":"Today we know that families are living further and further apart,"},{"time":405000,"text":"and that definitely takes a toll on family relationships"},{"time":407000,"text":"and family bonds over distance."},{"time":409000,"text":"For me, I have three young boys,"},{"time":411000,"text":"and I want them to have a really good relationship"},{"time":413000,"text":"with their grandparents."},{"time":415000,"text":"But my parents live thousands of miles away,"},{"time":417000,"text":"so they just don't get to see each other that often."},{"time":419000,"text":"We try Skype, we try phone calls,"},{"time":421000,"text":"but my boys are little -- they don't really want to talk;"},{"time":423000,"text":"they want to play."},{"time":425000,"text":"So I love the idea of thinking about robots"},{"time":427000,"text":"as a new kind of distance-play technology."},{"time":430000,"text":"I imagine a time not too far from now --"},{"time":433000,"text":"my mom can go to her computer,"},{"time":435000,"text":"open up a browser and jack into a little robot."},{"time":437000,"text":"And as grandma-bot,"},{"time":440000,"text":"she can now play, really play,"},{"time":442000,"text":"with my sons, with her grandsons,"},{"time":444000,"text":"in the real world with his real toys."},{"time":447000,"text":"I could imagine grandmothers being able to do social-plays"},{"time":449000,"text":"with their granddaughters, with their friends,"},{"time":451000,"text":"and to be able to share all kinds of other activities around the house,"},{"time":453000,"text":"like sharing a bedtime story."},{"time":455000,"text":"And through this technology,"},{"time":457000,"text":"being able to be an active participant"},{"time":459000,"text":"in their grandchildren's lives"},{"time":461000,"text":"in a way that's not possible today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":463000,"text":"Let's think about some other domains,"},{"time":465000,"text":"like maybe health."},{"time":467000,"text":"So in the United States today,"},{"time":469000,"text":"over 65 percent of people are either overweight or obese,"},{"time":472000,"text":"and now it's a big problem with our children as well."},{"time":474000,"text":"And we know that as you get older in life,"},{"time":476000,"text":"if you're obese when you're younger, that can lead to chronic diseases"},{"time":479000,"text":"that not only reduce your quality of life,"},{"time":481000,"text":"but are a tremendous economic burden on our health care system."},{"time":484000,"text":"But if robots can be engaging,"},{"time":486000,"text":"if we like to cooperate with robots,"},{"time":488000,"text":"if robots are persuasive,"},{"time":490000,"text":"maybe a robot can help you"},{"time":492000,"text":"maintain a diet and exercise program,"},{"time":494000,"text":"maybe they can help you manage your weight."},{"time":497000,"text":"Sort of like a digital Jiminy --"},{"time":499000,"text":"as in the well-known fairy tale --"},{"time":501000,"text":"a kind of friendly, supportive presence that's always there"},{"time":503000,"text":"to be able to help you make the right decision"},{"time":505000,"text":"in the right way at the right time"},{"time":507000,"text":"to help you form healthy habits."},{"time":509000,"text":"So we actually explored this idea in our lab."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511000,"text":"This is a robot, Autom."},{"time":513000,"text":"Cory Kidd developed this robot for his doctoral work."},{"time":516000,"text":"And it was designed to be a robot diet-and-exercise coach."},{"time":519000,"text":"It had a couple of simple non-verbal skills it could do."},{"time":521000,"text":"It could make eye contact with you."},{"time":523000,"text":"It could share information looking down at a screen."},{"time":525000,"text":"You'd use a screen interface to enter information,"},{"time":527000,"text":"like how many calories you ate that day,"},{"time":529000,"text":"how much exercise you got."},{"time":531000,"text":"And then it could help track that for you."},{"time":533000,"text":"And the robot spoke with a synthetic voice"},{"time":535000,"text":"to engage you in a coaching dialogue"},{"time":537000,"text":"modeled after trainers"},{"time":539000,"text":"and patients and so forth."},{"time":541000,"text":"And it would build a working alliance with you"},{"time":543000,"text":"through that dialogue."},{"time":545000,"text":"It could help you set goals and track your progress,"},{"time":547000,"text":"and it would help motivate you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549000,"text":"So an interesting question is,"},{"time":551000,"text":"does the social embodiment really matter? Does it matter that it's a robot?"},{"time":554000,"text":"Is it really just the quality of advice and information that matters?"},{"time":557000,"text":"To explore that question,"},{"time":559000,"text":"we did a study in the Boston area"},{"time":561000,"text":"where we put one of three interventions in people's homes"},{"time":564000,"text":"for a period of several weeks."},{"time":566000,"text":"One case was the robot you saw there, Autom."},{"time":569000,"text":"Another was a computer that ran the same touch-screen interface,"},{"time":572000,"text":"ran exactly the same dialogues."},{"time":574000,"text":"The quality of advice was identical."},{"time":576000,"text":"And the third was just a pen and paper log,"},{"time":578000,"text":"because that's the standard intervention you typically get"},{"time":580000,"text":"when you start a diet-and-exercise program."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583000,"text":"So one of the things we really wanted to look at"},{"time":586000,"text":"was not how much weight people lost,"},{"time":589000,"text":"but really how long they interacted with the robot."},{"time":592000,"text":"Because the challenge is not losing weight, it's actually keeping it off."},{"time":595000,"text":"And the longer you could interact with one of these interventions,"},{"time":598000,"text":"well that's indicative, potentially, of longer-term success."},{"time":601000,"text":"So the first thing I want to look at is how long,"},{"time":603000,"text":"how long did people interact with these systems."},{"time":605000,"text":"It turns out that people interacted with the robot"},{"time":607000,"text":"significantly more,"},{"time":609000,"text":"even though the quality of the advice was identical to the computer."},{"time":613000,"text":"When it asked people to rate it on terms of the quality of the working alliance,"},{"time":616000,"text":"people rated the robot higher"},{"time":618000,"text":"and they trusted the robot more."},{"time":620000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":622000,"text":"And when you look at emotional engagement,"},{"time":624000,"text":"it was completely different."},{"time":626000,"text":"People would name the robots."},{"time":628000,"text":"They would dress the robots."},{"time":630000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":632000,"text":"And even when we would come up to pick up the robots at the end of the study,"},{"time":635000,"text":"they would come out to the car and say good-bye to the robots."},{"time":637000,"text":"They didn't do this with a computer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639000,"text":"The last thing I want to talk about today"},{"time":641000,"text":"is the future of children's media."},{"time":643000,"text":"We know that kids spend a lot of time behind screens today,"},{"time":646000,"text":"whether it's television or computer games or whatnot."},{"time":649000,"text":"My sons, they love the screen. They love the screen."},{"time":652000,"text":"But I want them to play; as a mom, I want them to play,"},{"time":655000,"text":"like, real-world play."},{"time":657000,"text":"And so I have a new project in my group I wanted to present to you today"},{"time":660000,"text":"called Playtime Computing"},{"time":662000,"text":"that's really trying to think about how we can take"},{"time":664000,"text":"what's so engaging about digital media"},{"time":666000,"text":"and literally bring it off the screen"},{"time":668000,"text":"into the real world of the child,"},{"time":670000,"text":"where it can take on many of the properties of real-world play."},{"time":674000,"text":"So here's the first exploration of this idea,"},{"time":678000,"text":"where characters can be physical or virtual,"},{"time":681000,"text":"and where the digital content"},{"time":683000,"text":"can literally come off the screen"},{"time":685000,"text":"into the world and back."},{"time":687000,"text":"I like to think of this"},{"time":689000,"text":"as the Atari Pong"},{"time":691000,"text":"of this blended-reality play."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693000,"text":"But we can push this idea further."},{"time":695000,"text":"What if --"},{"time":697000,"text":"(Game) Nathan: Here it comes. Yay!"},{"time":700000,"text":"CB: -- the character itself could come into your world?"},{"time":703000,"text":"It turns out that kids love it"},{"time":705000,"text":"when the character becomes real and enters into their world."},{"time":708000,"text":"And when it's in their world,"},{"time":710000,"text":"they can relate to it and play with it in a way"},{"time":712000,"text":"that's fundamentally different from how they play with it on the screen."},{"time":714000,"text":"Another important idea is this notion"},{"time":716000,"text":"of persistence of character across realities."},{"time":719000,"text":"So changes that children make in the real world"},{"time":721000,"text":"need to translate to the virtual world."},{"time":723000,"text":"So here, Nathan has changed the letter A to the number 2."},{"time":726000,"text":"You can imagine maybe these symbols"},{"time":728000,"text":"give the characters special powers when it goes into the virtual world."},{"time":731000,"text":"So they are now sending the character back into that world."},{"time":734000,"text":"And now it's got number power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":737000,"text":"And then finally, what I've been trying to do here"},{"time":739000,"text":"is create a really immersive experience for kids,"},{"time":742000,"text":"where they really feel like they are part of that story,"},{"time":745000,"text":"a part of that experience."},{"time":747000,"text":"And I really want to spark their imaginations"},{"time":749000,"text":"the way mine was sparked as a little girl watching \"Star Wars.\""},{"time":752000,"text":"But I want to do more than that."},{"time":754000,"text":"I actually want them to create those experiences."},{"time":757000,"text":"I want them to be able to literally build their imagination"},{"time":759000,"text":"into these experiences and make them their own."},{"time":761000,"text":"So we've been exploring a lot of ideas"},{"time":763000,"text":"in telepresence and mixed reality"},{"time":765000,"text":"to literally allow kids to project their ideas into this space"},{"time":768000,"text":"where other kids can interact with them"},{"time":770000,"text":"and build upon them."},{"time":772000,"text":"I really want to come up with new ways of children's media"},{"time":775000,"text":"that foster creativity and learning and innovation."},{"time":778000,"text":"I think that's very, very important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":781000,"text":"So this is a new project."},{"time":783000,"text":"We've invited a lot of kids into this space,"},{"time":785000,"text":"and they think it's pretty cool."},{"time":788000,"text":"But I can tell you, the thing that they love the most"},{"time":790000,"text":"is the robot."},{"time":792000,"text":"What they care about is the robot."},{"time":795000,"text":"Robots touch something deeply human within us."},{"time":798000,"text":"And so whether they're helping us"},{"time":800000,"text":"to become creative and innovative,"},{"time":802000,"text":"or whether they're helping us"},{"time":804000,"text":"to feel more deeply connected despite distance,"},{"time":806000,"text":"or whether they are our trusted sidekick"},{"time":808000,"text":"who's helping us attain our personal goals"},{"time":810000,"text":"in becoming our highest and best selves,"},{"time":812000,"text":"for me, robots are all about people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":815000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":817000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}